name: London
description: It's lights out and away we go, we're on our way to Sydney with a quick pit stop in Dubai.

name: Dubai
description:
To break up the journey (and save some money) we booked a flight with a 20 hour layover in Dubai. Through the Emirates Dubai Connect program we got a night in a hotel for free so we had a short nap and then got ready to explore a bit.

It was over 40c so even the short 8 minute walk to the Metro station was quite a challenge. We kept things fairly simple and went to the Dubai Mall to check out the aquarium, Burj Khalifa, fountain show and the air conditioning. The scale of everything in Dubai is pretty crazy and while we didn't get to see much of it was nice to experience a new country and culture, albeit briefly.

name: Sydney
description: Our first stop in Oz in s̶u̶n̶n̶y̶ Sydney. It’s not an exaggeration to say that it rained pretty much non-stop during our stay, so much so that we ran out of dry clothes. Between the rain and the jet lag we probably didn’t quite get the start to our trip we were expecting but we got out there and saw the main sights, safe in the knowledge we planned to return later in the year.

name: Mount Remarkable National Park
description:
Stop number 1 of our great Australian road trip! A few hours out of Adelaide, we spent a couple of nights camping in a national park. We were greeted with Kangaroos, Emus and Kookaburras wandering around camp, and so many stars in the sky at night!

We did a nice walk through the park, up to a viewpoint, and enjoyed the peace and quiet after a month or so in cities.

name: Spud's Roadhouse
description: Our first roadhouse and our first experience of quite how empty parts of the outback are. We met an interesting guy in the van parked next to us who showed us his opal collection, made some dinner on our stove and then had a few drinks inside to stay warm.

name: Coober Pedy
description: One of the places we were most looking forward to visiting. It was once a busy opal mining town and can get so hot that many locals live in caves to stay cool. We got to have a look around some of the old mines and stayed underground!

name: Marla
description: Another night on the road, another roadhouse stopover. To keep these balanced and not only containing the good stuff we were besieged by flies here and learnt to perfect the Aussie wave.

name: Erldunda Roadhouse
description: Not too much to say about this, it was an overnight stop on our way to Alice Springs. They had a camel.

name: Banka Banka
description: A great little camp at a farm homestead. They had an Indian food truck which did a great paneer curry and roti, and music around the camp fire.

name: Daly Waters
description:
The Famous Daly Waters pub. We spent 2 nights here in one of the motel rooms to refresh and get a chance to wash off some of the red dust that's accumulating.

Lots of interesting things around town, great garlic bread in the pub, and some great happy hour deals.

name: Daly Waters
description:
Since we were passing Daly Waters again on our way back down we decided to stop in for more garlic bread and $5 wines. This time we were treated to the eccentric owner on his mobility scooter telling us the history of the pub accompanied by his menagerie of animals.

It was up to 35 degrees during the day which made for a sweaty night's sleep. We went to bed to news of the Queen's deteriorating health and woke up to news of her death. A very strange place to be hearing the news.

name: Barkly Homestead
description: A roadhouse in the middle of the outback. Happy hour wasn’t as good as Daly Waters but we enjoyed a few stubbies whilst watching the news coverage about the Queen.

name: Cloncurry
description: Another night on the road. We pulled up in town with no booking and managed to get an unpowered patch of dirt at a caravan park. It had a pool and a decent kitchen though so we swam, showered, ate, and got an early night ready for more driving in the morning.

name: Karumba
description: We started the day with no plans as to where to spend the night. On the drive James found a holiday park with  a caravan to rent available for the night, so we booked it and headed there. Turned out to be a very picturesque spot. We grabbed some fish and chips and watched the sunset before stopping in for a quick drink at the pub.

name: Mount Surprise
description: SURPRISE! We spent a couple of nights in the forest here. The park had a nice train-themed bar/restaurant and a pool surrounded by the local resident kangaroos. We hiked around an old volcanic crater and spotted our first snake of the year! A little red-bellied black snake crossed the path right in front of us.

name: Port Douglas
description:
After a full on week of driving we finally hit the east coast and now have a few days chilling in port Douglas. It’s much more of a holiday resort type town than the places we’ve been recently, lots of fancy hotels and restaurants we can’t afford!

We went on a few walks to viewpoints, ate pizza watching the sunset, visited the wildlife park, and Nicole did yoga on the beach one morning.

name: Babinda
description: As boulders go these are right up there.

name: Mackay
description: Not much to say about this one, we arrived in town fairly late and stayed in a motel.

name: Hervey Bay
description: There was a jetty apparently, can’t remember much else. I’m writing this 6 months on, cut me some slack.

name: Brisbane
description: Overnight stay in a hotel (pub) before we flew out to Bali early the next morning.

name: South Yarra
description: Another house sit, just a short one this weekend with a very lazy goldendoodle called Penny. We dragged (quite literally sometimes) her out for a few walks and played some tennis. Explored South Yarra a little, probably one of the nicest Melbourne suburbs we’ve seen so far!

name: Lynbrook
description:
We had a couple of days to fill in-between house sits and managed to find a very reasonably priced BnB south east of Melbourne, it even came with two cats which was a nice bonus.

The main thing we did was visit the royal botanic gardens in Cranbourne which were very impressive.

name: Black Rock
description:
We had a very chilled week doing a house sit and looking after a very excitable young toy poodle called Jasper. We stayed in a really nice apartment that was literally on beach road on the coast south east of Melbourne.

We took Jasper out for lots of walks along the beach, did a bit of work and tried to plan where we were going next!

name: Lynbrook
description: Back in lynbrook at the same b&b again since it was cheap and very nice. Didn’t do much this time since it was just a quick overnighted before heading out into the mountains tomorrow.

name: Ararat
description: We had a couple of nights until we needed to be back in the city and found a cheap holiday cabin in this little town. Turned out to be a great stop - lovely park, nice tennis courts for a hit, and we did a cellar tour at a local winery that was really interesting! They claimed to be the birthplace of sparkling red wine.

name: St Kilda
description: Quick stop back in Melbourne to watch Maisie Peters in St Kilda, and see a woman about some cats. We spent a morning wandering Albert park where they’re currently building the track for next month’s Grand Prix. That’s the next time we’ll be back in the city!

name: Jamieson Creek
description: Just one night at a bush campsite but we caught a lovely sunset and watched the wallabies hop around camp. Woke up to one of Nicole’s sandals halfway across the site and all chewed up - maybe a possum?

name: Dartmoor
description: Just a quick overnight stop in Dartmoor in a free camping spot. The town is very small but had a nice pub and some interesting tree sculptures.

name: Robe
description: Beautiful little beach town on the limestone coast in south SA. Spent a few days relaxing and recharging after the great ocean road. The highlight of Robe was probably long beach (aptly named at around 12km long) where you can drive right along the sand and bag yourself a quiet spot with no one else around. Sunset over the water was spectacular.

name: Haddon
description: Just a quick overnighter on the way back to Melbourne. Free camping in a park in a tiny town. Windy and Cold, but we got a nice sunset, cooked up a curry and did I mention it was FREE?!

name: South Melbourne
description: Back in the city! 2 weeks house sitting, Grand Prix, James' family visiting, then we'll say goodbye to Melbourne for good (for this trip anyway!)

name: Spring Beach
description: We splashed out on an Airbnb with a tennis court for James’ birthday, no regrets, it was amazing.

name: Ouse
description: An overnight stop in a lakeside free camp as we made our way to Western Tas. It was just us, one other van.. and the local feral kitties.

name: Queenstown
description: An unscheduled but very picturesque overnight stop. Nigel gave us a bit of a scare during the day so we got him a check up and a few new spark plugs. At first we were sceptical when parts of Australia were referred to as being “alpine” but this really did feel like a mountain town.

name: Ulverstone
description: Not the most exciting stop, we caught up on some life admin and had a wander around the town and along the beach.

name: Bass Strait
description: After an amazing couple of weeks in Tasmania we set sail back to the mainland.

name: Kingston SE
description: One of our longest days of driving, all the way from Geelong after getting off the boat at 7am across to Kingston in SA to stay in the cheapest cabin around, straight from the 1970’s. The beach was covered in a 30cm thick carpet of seaweed, but the sunset was still pretty good. Visited Larry the big lobster on our way out the next morning.

name: Coorong
description: One final night bush camping in Nigel. We had the entire camp site to ourselves, got to see a lovely sunset while we cooked dinner and in the morning it poured with rain, a fitting send off.

name: Adelaide
description: Just under a year later and we’re back to where our road trip began. We had one final stay in a holiday park before a short flat share / pet sit with Alfie the cat. We sold or donated as much of our stuff as we could, including Nigel and did our best to prepare for living out of backpacks again.

name: Perth
description: Our final stop in Australia. We weren’t planning to visit WA initially and this definitely wasn’t enough time but it was nice to see some of it. Freemantle seemed like it would be a nice place to live with the convenience of a big city nearby but a more laid back feel.

name: Kuala Lumpur
description: We got a coach up from Singapore for a very hot and sweaty 3 nights in KL. We did our best to get out and explore but it did feel a bit like we were mostly filling time between trips to one of the many shopping centres to cool down 🥵. The highlight has to be this amazing bar we found on top of a building which used to be a helipad, incredible views.

name: Ko Phi Phi
description: We didn’t know how much time we’d end up spending on Phi Phi since we’d heard it was a bit of a party Island. But in the end we spent a week and didn’t party at all! It was nice being somewhere you could walk everywhere, no taxis or mopeds, and relaxed Island life.

name: Rawai
description: Not the most eventful week as we were both sick for most of it. We had a nice Airbnb apartment with a pool though and just relaxed and when we could manage it went out for breakfast or dinner. It seemed like a really nice area so it’s a shame we couldn’t see more of it.

name: London
description: 378 days later and we’re back 😅
